(2) Where there is a contravention under subsection (1) the Board may require the hotel-keeper , by notice in writing, to correct the contravention within a period, not being less than thirty days, and if the hotel-keeper fails to do so to the satisfaction of the Board within the specified period, the Board may revoke in writing the hotel licence or the hotel manager's licence , but the revocation of either licence shall not take effect until the expiration of thirty days from the date of the notice to revoke: Provided that where the nature or extent of the contravention is serious, the Board may order that the revocation of the hotel licence or hotel manager's licence shall take effect immediately.
