(1) A person aggrieved by— (a) a refusal by the Board to grant a licence or to permit the transfer of an hotel licence ; (b) the cancellation of a licence by the Board ; or (c) the grading or re-grading of an hotel by the Board ; may, within thirty days from the date of receipt of notification of the refusal, cancellation, grading or re-grading, appeal to the Minister, who may confirm, vary or set aside the decision of the Board , or send it back to the Board for further consideration.
